content.text:
Paris is the capital of France. This is a well-established historical and political fact. Paris has been France's capital since 987 CE when Hugh Capet made the city his seat of power. As France's capital, Paris is:

1. The seat of the French national government
2. The location of most major government institutions
3. The country's largest city and economic center
4. The official residence of the French President (Élysée Palace)
5. Home to the French Parliament (National Assembly and Senate)
